comment: Just been watching a House marathon. Season 4 was really something- for my money, the best work by writers and cast alike in the whole series. Right up to [spoiler] Amber's death, which I just saw for the first time in all these years and it has lost none of its power. Anne Dudek does a great job in this scene, too, giving Amber a whole new side in just a few moments. House, of course, is wildly inconsistent through this episode, the season, and the series, in his worldview and expectations. An original, and Laurie does some of his best work as House right here.
